olive oil
2 potato
½ tin Pineapple Slices
1 packet chicken breast
1 sachet Mild Caribbean Jerk Seasoning
20 g butter
2 Butter Burger Buns
1 bag spinach & rocket mix
1 packet mayonnaise
drizzle vinegar (balsamic or white wine)

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced. Cut potato into wedges, then place on a lined oven tray.
• Drizzle with olive oil, season with salt and toss to coat. Spread out evenly, then bake until tender, 20-25 minutes.

• Meanwhile, reserve some pineapple juice (1 tbs for 2 people / 2 tbs for 4 people) and drain pineapple slices (see ingredients).
• Place your hand flat on top of chicken breast and slice through horizontally to make two thin steaks.
• In a medium bowl, combine chicken, mild Caribbean jerk seasoning and a drizzle of olive oil. Toss to coat.

• Heat a large frying pan over high heat. Cook pineapple slices until lightly charred, 2-3 minutes each side.
• Transfer to a plate.

• Return the frying pan to medium-high heat with a generous drizzle of olive oil. Cook chicken until cooked through, 3-5 minutes each side.
• Remove pan from heat, add reserved pineapple juice and the butter, turning chicken to coat.

TIP: Chicken is cooked through when it's no longer pink inside.

• Meanwhile, halve burger buns and bake directly on a wire oven rack until heated through, 2-3 minutes.
• In a second medium bowl, combine spinach & rocket mix and a drizzle of vinegar and olive oil. Season to taste.

• Spread tops of burger buns with mayonnaise.
• Top with chicken, charred pineapple and salad leaves.
• Serve with potato wedges, any remaining mayo and salad. Enjoy!